@giorgioarmani built the blueprint for the power blazer. ARMANI/Archivio brings it back into focus.
Marking 50 years of the house, the project reworks the archive with a modern lens. The latest drop revisits 13 looks from 1979 to 1994, reproduced with precision and released for the first time.
At the centre is the jacket, fluid, exact, and quietly subversive. The silhouettes that reshaped tailoring still feel effortless now. More April Fashion news at the link in bio.

